{{Orphan|date=June 2018}}
'''Toilet Revolution'''({{zh|s=厕所革命}}) is a campaign in [[China]] aiming at improving the sanitary conditions in [[Mainland China]]. In 2015, [[Xi Jinping]], [[General Secretary of the Communist Party of China]], announced that China is going to improve the sanitary conditions in tourist attractions, which once complained by foreign travelers. During 2015 to 2017, over 68,000 [[public toilet]]s were reconstructed in China. In 2017, a re-construction to other 64,000 public toilets was planned.<ref name=Cheang2017>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2017/11/28/chinas-toilet-revolution-will-give-domestic-tourism-boost-xi-says.html|title=Toilet revolution': China has its sight set on reforming its bathrooms|publisher=CNBC|author=Cheang Ming|year=2017}}</ref><ref name=Wong2017>{{cite web|author=Maggie Hiufu Wong|url=https://edition.cnn.com/travel/article/china-toilet-revolution/index.html|title=China to get extreme toilet makeover to boost tourism|publisher=CNN|year=2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|author1=Shikun Cheng|author2=etal|title=Toilet revolution in China|journal=Journal of Environmental Management|year=2017|doi=10.1016/j.jenvman.2017.09.043}}</ref>
In 2017, The campaign was expanded. The authorities are going to improve the poor sanitary conditions in rural area in China. State Media in China says that the poor sanitary conditions in rural area contribute to spreading of diseases like [[malaria]] and the campaign is aiming at solve such problems.<ref name=CD2017>{{cite web|url=http://china.chinadaily.com.cn/2017-11/29/content_35121846.htm|title=习近平：农村也要来个"厕所革命"(Xi Jinping: Toilet Revolution should also be unfolded in rural area)|publisher=中国日报([[China Daily]])|year=2017|language=zh}}</ref>
